    .three-column-layout {\n            display: grid;\n            grid-template-columns: 40% 35% 25%;\n            gap: 15px;\n        }\n\n        section {\n            background-color: #ffffff;\n            border: 1px solid #d4d4d4;\n            padding: 10px;\n        }\n\n        .section-header {\n            background-color: #ff6600;\n            padding: 5px 10px;\n            margin: -10px -10px 10px -10px;\n            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\n            font-weight: bold;\n            font-size: 11pt;\n        }\n\n        .item {\n            margin-bottom: 15px;\n            padding-bottom: 15px;\n            border-bottom: 1px solid #eeeeee;\n        }\n\n        .item:last-child {\n            border-bottom: none;\n            margin-bottom: 0;\n            padding-bottom: 0;\n        }\n\n        .item-title {\n            font-size: 10pt;\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\n        }\n\n        .item-title a {\n            color: #000000;\n        }\n\n        .item-title a:visited {\n            color: #828282;\n        }\n\n        .item-description {\n            font-size: 9pt;\n            color: #444444;\n            margin-bottom: 5px;\n            line-height: 1.4;\n        }\n\n        .item-meta {\n            font-size: 8pt;\n            color: #828282;\n        }\n\n        .tag {\n            display: inline-block;\n            background-color: #f0f0f0;\n            padding: 2px 6px;\n            margin: 2px 2px 0 0;\n            font-size: 8pt;\n            border-radius: 2px;\n        }\n\n        .source {\n            color: #828282;\n            font-size: 8pt;\n        }\n\n        .update-badge {\n            display: inline-block;\n            padding: 2px 6px;\n            margin-right: 5px;\n            font-size: 7pt;\n            border-radius: 2px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n        }\n\n        .update-badge.feature {\n            background-color: #e6f7ff;\n            color: #0050b3;\n        }\n\n        .update-badge.bugfix {\n            background-color: #fff7e6;\n            color: #d46b08;\n        }\n\n        .update-badge.release {\n            background-color: #f6ffed;\n            color: #389e0d;\n        }\n\n        .update-badge.announcement {\n            background-color: #f9f0ff;\n            color: #722ed1;\n        }\n\n        .insight-author {\n            font-weight: bold;\n            color: #000000;\n        }\n\n        .insight-topics {\n            margin-top: 5px;\n        }\n\n        .community-feedback {\n            margin-top: 8px;\n            padding: 8px;\n            background-color: #f9f9f9;\n            border-left: 3px solid #ff6600;\n            font-size: 8pt;\n            font-style: italic;\n        }\n\n        .community-feedback-source {\n            display: block;\n            margin-top: 3px;\n            font-size: 8pt;\n            font-style: normal;\n            color: #828282;\n        }\n\n        footer {\n            background-color: #f6f6ef;\n            border-top: 1px solid #d4d4d4;\n            padding: 15px 10px;\n            margin-top: 20px;\n        }\n\n        .footer-content {\n            max-width: 1200px;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n            text-align: center;\n            font-size: 8pt;\n            color: #828282;\n        }\n\n        .footer-content a {\n            color: #828282;\n            margin: 0 10px;\n        }\n\n        .footer-content a:hover {\n            color: #000000;\n        }\n\n        .empty-state {\n            text-align: center;\n            padding: 30px 10px;\n            color: #828282;\n            font-style: italic;\n        }\n\n        @media print {\n            body {\n                background-color: #ffffff;\n            }\n\n            section {\n                page-break-inside: avoid;\n            }\n\n            .nav-bar {\n                display: none;\n            }\n        }\n\n        @media (max-width: 900px) {\n            .three-column-layout {\n                grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n            }\n\n            .item {\n                margin-bottom: 20px;\n            }\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <header>\n        <div class=\"header-content\">\n            <div class=\"header-title\">Agentic Coding Daily Report</div>\n            <div class=\"header-date\">March 3, 2026</div>\n        </div>\n    </header>\n\n    <nav class=\"nav-bar\">\n        <div class=\"nav-content\">\n            <div class=\"nav-links\">\n                <a href=\"#new-products\">New Products</a>\n                <a href=\"#whitelist-updates\">Product Updates</a>\n                <a href=\"#technical-insights\">Technical Insights</a>\n                <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-agent-sdk\">GitHub</a>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </nav>\n\n    <main>\n        <div class=\"three-column-layout\">\n            <section class=\"new-products\" id=\"new-products\">\n                <div class=\"section-header\">New Products (0)</div>\n                <div class=\"empty-state\">No new products found in this research cycle.</div>\n            </section>\n\n            <section class=\"whitelist-updates\" id=\"whitelist-updates\">\n                <div class=\"section-header\">Product Updates (12)</div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://claude.ai/code\">Claude Opus 4.6 with 1M Token Context</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        <span class=\"update-badge feature\">FEATURE</span>\n                        Anthropic released Claude Opus 4.6 with an experimental 1 million token context window, significantly improving long-context queries, reasoning, and planning capabilities.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">Claude Code | Feb 20, 2026</div>\n                    <div class=\"community-feedback\">\n                        \"Community discussion on whether AI represents the future of programming assistance, with many developers expressing excitement about 1M token context for large codebase understanding\"\n                        <span class=\"community-feedback-source\">— Hacker News - Stop generating, start thinking</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://github.com/features/copilot\">GPT-5.3-Codex Model Integration</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        <span class=\"update-badge feature\">FEATURE</span>\n                        GitHub rolled out OpenAI's GPT-5.3-Codex model to Copilot, delivering approximately 25% better performance for agentic coding tasks. Available for Pro, Pro+, Business, and Enterprise users.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">GitHub Copilot | Feb 20, 2026</div>\n                    <div class=\"community-feedback\">\n                        \"Community discussion about improving LLM coding effectiveness through optimizations, with many users noting that model improvements like GPT-5.3-Codex significantly enhance real-world coding performance\"\n                        <span class=\"community-feedback-source\">— Hacker News - Improving 15 LLMs at Coding</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://m.oschina.net/news/372581\">OpenAI Codex CLI GPT-5.2 Integration</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        <span class=\"update-badge feature\">FEATURE</span>\n                        Codex CLI upgraded to GPT-5.2-Codex model with 40% faster inference, 400K token input support, and 50+ programming languages. New macOS desktop application and JetBrains integration.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">Codex CLI | Feb 19, 2026</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/releases/tag/v2.1.47\">v2.1.47 - Major Bug Fixes and Windows Improvements</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        <span class=\"update-badge bugfix\">BUGFIX</span>\n                        Extensive fixes for Windows terminal rendering, file writing to preserve trailing blank lines, improved VS Code plan preview with auto-updates, better memory usage in long-running sessions, faster startup performance (~500ms improvement).\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">Claude Code | Feb 18, 2026</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-code/releases/tag/v2.1.45\">v2.1.45 - Claude Sonnet 4.6 Support</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        <span class=\"update-badge feature\">FEATURE</span>\n                        Adds support for Claude Sonnet 4.6, introduces SDK rate limit info types, custom spinner tips override, improved startup performance, better memory usage for large shell command output.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">Claude Code | Feb 18, 2026</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://github.com/continuedev/continue/releases/tag/v1.3.32-vscode\">v1.3.32 - Latest VS Code Extension Release</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        <span class=\"update-badge release\">RELEASE</span>\n                        Continue v1.3.32 released with updates for VS Code extension including Alpine x64, Darwin ARM64, and Linux ARM64 builds.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">Continue | Feb 18, 2026</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/releases\">Version 0.86.0 - GPT-5 and Grok-4 Support</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        <span class=\"update-badge feature\">FEATURE</span>\n                        Aider v0.86.0 added support for OpenAI GPT-5 models and xAI Grok-4, expanding the range of supported AI coding assistants.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">Aider | Feb 17, 2026</div>\n                    <div class=\"community-feedback\">\n                        \"Discussion examining how AI coding tools don't actually reduce workload but instead require skilled programmers to be more effective.\"\n                        <span class=\"community-feedback-source\">— Hacker News - AI doesn't reduce work, it intensifies it</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://continue.dev/blog\">Chiseling: The Art of Polishing Vibe Code</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        <span class=\"update-badge announcement\">BLOG</span>\n                        Continue published a blog post about 'Chiseling: The Art of Polishing Vibe Code', discussing techniques for refining AI-generated code to production quality.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">Continue | Feb 17, 2026</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2026/Feb/16/claude-code-desktop/\">Desktop App Image Viewing Feature</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        <span class=\"update-badge feature\">FEATURE</span>\n                        The Claude Code desktop app shows images that Claude is viewing via its Read tool, providing visual preview of what the AI is working on.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">Claude Code | Feb 16, 2026</div>\n                    <div class=\"community-feedback\">\n                        \"Someone has to prompt the Claudes, talk to customers, coordinate with other teams, decide what to build next. Engineering is changing and great engineers are more important than ever.\"\n                        <span class=\"community-feedback-source\">— Boris Cherny (Claude Code Creator)</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://openai.com/index/introducing-gpt-5-3-codex-spark/\">GPT-5.3-Codex-Spark: Ultra-fast model</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        <span class=\"update-badge feature\">FEATURE</span>\n                        OpenAI's latest coding model with improved processing speed and tool execution time, including enhanced performance on Terminal-Bench 2.0. Ultra-fast model optimized for real-time coding.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">Codex CLI | Feb 16, 2026</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://devblogs.microsoft.com/dotnet/github-copilot-testing-for-dotnet-available-in-visual-studio/\">Copilot Testing for .NET Generally Available</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        <span class=\"update-badge release\">RELEASE</span>\n                        GitHub Copilot Testing for .NET moved from preview to general availability in Visual Studio 2026 v18.3, bringing AI-powered unit test generation to .NET developers.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">GitHub Copilot | Feb 16, 2026</div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://openai.com/codex-app\">OpenAI Codex App for macOS</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        <span class=\"update-badge feature\">FEATURE</span>\n                        Standalone AI coding workspace designed specifically for agent-based software development. Functions as a desktop command center with multi-agent workflows, running multiple AI coding agents in parallel.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\">Codex CLI | Feb 15, 2026</div>\n                    <div class=\"community-feedback\">\n                        \"Hacker News discussion with ironic title exploring approaches for AI skeptics to effectively use LLMs for coding.\"\n                        <span class=\"community-feedback-source\">— Hacker News - The AI hater's guide to code with LLMs</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </section>\n\n            <section class=\"technical-insights\" id=\"technical-insights\">\n                <div class=\"section-header\">Technical Insights (9)</div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://www.showapi.com/news/article/69a47b474ddd79ab6720ce52\">AI Programming Partner: Building 2026 LLM Collaborative Workflows</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Systematic guide on using LLMs as reliable programming partners. Covers specifications, task decomposition, model selection, context engineering.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\"><span class=\"insight-author\">万维易源</span> | Feb 28, 2026</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">LLM workflows</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">AI programming</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://juejin.cn/post/7611006514892242963\">AI's Next Steps: 5 Trends to Watch in 2026</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Comprehensive analysis covering evolution of AI coding agents and specialized LLMs trained for coding. Explains how agents understand project structures and debugging.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\"><span class=\"insight-author\">稀土掘金</span> | Feb 27, 2026</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">AI trends 2026</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">AI agents</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://mp.ofweek.com/ai/a556714706507\">AI Coding Market Analysis: Product Surge But Startup Opportunities Closing</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Analysis noting product surge in early 2026, but warning opportunities for startups are closing. Major acquisitions: Cursor $900M funding, Google acquired Windsurf for $2.4B.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\"><span class=\"insight-author\">OFweek AI</span> | Feb 26, 2026</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">market analysis</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">startups</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@Fireship\">How to Make Vibe Coding Not Suck - 7 Essential MCP Servers</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Fireship video on AI coding state, highlighting 7 essential MCP servers to avoid 'prompt hell treadmill' and improve AI coding reliability.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\"><span class=\"insight-author\">Fireship</span> | Feb 25, 2026</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Vibe Coding</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">MCP servers</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://new.qq.com/rain/a/LNK2025081008329400\">Claude Code Usage Experience - 1.5 Months of Intensive Vibe Coding</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Detailed analysis of 'Vibe Coding' after 1.5 months of Claude Code usage. Explains what LLMs excel at vs where they struggle.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\"><span class=\"insight-author\">喵神 (Miao Shen)</span> | Feb 25, 2026</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Claude Code</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Vibe Coding</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://news.qq.com/rain/a/20260224A06NX300\">Stanford Launches Vibe Coding Tutorial - AI Development Course</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Stanford released new course on 'Coding LLMs and AI Development' covering LLM training, prompt engineering, and open-source tools like GitNexus.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\"><span class=\"insight-author\">Stanford University</span> | Feb 24, 2026</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Vibe Coding</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">education</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://twitter.com/karpathy\">AI Programming Reached Critical Threshold in December 2025 - Andrej Karpathy</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Karpathy declared AI programming underwent fundamental change in December 2025. Before: 'basically useless.' After: paradigm shift to '80% Agent-coded + 20% human refinement.'\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\"><span class=\"insight-author\">Andrej Karpathy</span> | Feb 24, 2026</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">Vibe Coding</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">paradigm shift</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://blog.csdn.net/wangzhao0012/article/details/158349495\">Karpathy's Six Key LLM Breakthroughs of 2025</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        Annual summary highlighting six breakthroughs: RLVR, Jagged Intelligence, Cursor's Next-Gen App Layer, Claude Code Local Agents, Vibe Coding, and Nano Banana LLM GUI.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\"><span class=\"insight-author\">Andrej Karpathy</span> | Feb 24, 2026</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">LLM breakthroughs</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">RLVR</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n\n                <div class=\"item\">\n                    <div class=\"item-title\">\n                        <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@lexfridman\">Lex Fridman Podcast #482: Pavel Durov on Freedom, Censorship, and Technology</a>\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-description\">\n                        In-depth 4 hour 34 minute interview with Telegram founder Pavel Durov covering philosophy, freedom of speech, censorship, money, power, and human nature.\n                    </div>\n                    <div class=\"item-meta\"><span class=\"insight-author\">Lex Fridman</span> | Feb 24, 2026</div>\n                    <div class=\"insight-topics\">\n                        <span class=\"tag\">podcast</span>\n                        <span class=\"tag\">technology</span>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </section>\n        </div>\n    </main>\n\n    <footer>\n        <div class=\"footer-content\">\n            <a href=\"https://github.com/anthropics/claude-agent-sdk\">Claude Agent SDK</a>\n            <a href=\"https://claude.ai/code\">Claude Code</a>\n            <a href=\"#\">Privacy Policy</a>\n            <a href=\"#\">Terms of Service</a>\n            <div style=\"margin-top: 10px;\">\n                <em>Report generated by Agent Code Daily - Powered by Claude Agent SDK</em>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </footer>\n</body>\n</html>"
}

