89→            .three-column-layout {\n   190→                grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n   191→            }\n   192→\n   193→            section {\n   194→                margin-bottom: 15px;\n   195→            }\n   196→        }\n   197→\n   198→        @media print {\n   199→            body {\n   200→                background-color: #ffffff;\n   201→            }\n   202→\n   203→            section {\n   204→                border: 1px solid #000000;\n   205→                page-break-inside: avoid;\n   206→            }\n   207→\n   208→            a {\n   209→                color: #000000;\n   210→                text-decoration: underline;\n   211→            }\n   212→        }\n   213→    </style>\n   214→</head>\n   215→<body>\n   216→    <header>\n   217→        <h1>Agentic Coding Research Report</h1>\n   218→        <div class=\"date\">2026-03-03</div>\n   219→    </header>\n   220→\n   221→    <main class=\"three-column-layout\">\n   222→        <section class=\"new-products\">\n   223→            <h2>New Products</h2>\n   224→            <div class=\"empty-state\">No new products reported for this period.</div>\n   225→        </section>\n   226→\n   227→        <section class=\"whitelist-updates\">\n   228→            <h2>Whitelist Updates</h2>\n   229→\n   230→            <div class=\"item\">\n   231→                <div class=\"item-title\">\n   232→                    <a href=\"https://claude.ai/code\" target=\"_blank\">Claude Code</a>\n   233→                </div>\n   234→                <div class=\"item-description\">\n   235→                    Remote Control Feature Launch - Anthropic launched remote control functionality for Claude Code, initially available for Claude Max subscribers with planned expansion to Claude Pro users.\n   236→                </div>\n   237→                <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   238→                    <span class=\"update-type\">feature</span>\n   239→                    <span>2026-02-25</span>\n   240→                </div>\n   241→                <div class=\"feedback\">\n   242→                    \"Boris Cherny (Claude Code Creator) claimed he hadn't manually written a single line of code in 2 months. His team's workflow: '49 PRs in two days' - nearly 100% of development work done by Claude Code\"\n   243→                    <span class=\"feedback-source\">— Industry interview/podcast</span>\n   244→                </div>\n   245→                <div class=\"feedback\">\n   246→                    \"Andrej Karpathy expressed feeling 'more behind than ever' as a programmer, noting that a 'magnitude 9 earthquake' was hitting the programming industry\"\n   247→                    <span class=\"feedback-source\">— X/Twitter</span>\n   248→                </div>\n   249→            </div>\n   250→\n   251→            <div class=\"item\">\n   252→                <div class=\"item-title\">\n   253→                    <a href=\"https://geminicli.com/docs/changelogs/\" target=\"_blank\">Gemini CLI</a>\n   254→                </div>\n   255→                <div class=\"item-description\">\n   256→                    Version 0.22.0 - Gemini 3 for Free Tier - Gemini CLI V0.22.0 opened Gemini 3 series models (Pro and Flash) to all Free Tier users. Also released Conductor extension for project management and Endor Labs extension.\n   257→                </div>\n   258→                <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   259→                    <span class=\"update-type\">feature</span>\n   260→                    <span>2026-02-22</span>\n   261→                </div>\n   262→            </div>\n   263→\n   264→            <div class=\"item\">\n   265→                <div class=\"item-title\">\n   266→                    <a href=\"https://cursor.sh\" target=\"_blank\">Cursor</a>\n   267→                </div>\n   268→                <div class=\"item-description\">\n   269→                    Major AI Agent Feature Update - Cursor released a substantial update targeting AI Agent functionality on February 24, 2026, described as throwing down the gauntlet in the competitive AI programming tools market.\n   270→                </div>\n   271→                <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   272→                    <span class=\"update-type\">feature</span>\n   273→                    <span>2026-02-24</span>\n   274→                </div>\n   275→                <div class=\"feedback\">\n   276→                    \"Even with identical models, Claude Code outperforms Cursor in certain scenarios. The terminal Agent product form of Claude Code better fits complex engineering needs\"\n   277→                    <span class=\"feedback-source\">— Developer comparison</span>\n   278→                </div>\n   279→            </div>\n   280→\n   281→            <div class=\"item\">\n   282→                <div class=\"item-title\">\n   283→                    <a href=\"https://github.com/MaheshTechnicals/Windsurf-Termux\" target=\"_blank\">Windsurf</a>\n   284→                </div>\n   285→                <div class=\"item-description\">\n   286→                    ARM64 and Termux Support - Windsurf v1.3 released for ARM64 devices, enabling installation of Windsurf IDE on Android Termux and ARM64 Linux.\n   287→                </div>\n   288→                <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   289→                    <span class=\"update-type\">feature</span>\n   290→                    <span>2026-02-17</span>\n   291→                </div>\n   292→            </div>\n   293→        </section>\n   294→\n   295→        <section class=\"technical-insights\">\n   296→            <h2>Technical Insights</h2>\n   297→\n   298→            <div class=\"item\">\n   299→                <div class=\"item-title\">\n   300→                    <a href=\"https://www.showapi.com/news/article/69a47b474ddd79ab6720ce52\" target=\"_blank\">AI Programming Partner: Building 2026 LLM Collaborative Workflows</a>\n   301→                </div>\n   302→                <div class=\"item-description\">\n   303→                    A systematic guide on using LLMs as reliable programming partners in 2026. Covers writing clear specifications, scientific task decomposition, dynamic model selection, context engineering, and integration of automation and testing mechanisms.\n   304→                </div>\n   305→                <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   306→                    <span class=\"source-badge\">Technical Blog</span>\n   307→                    <span>万维易源</span>\n   308→                    <span>| 2026-02-28</span>\n   309→                </div>\n   310→                <div>\n   311→                    <span class=\"tag\">LLM workflows</span>\n   312→                    <span class=\"tag\">AI programming</span>\n   313→                    <span class=\"tag\">task decomposition</span>\n   314→                </div>\n   315→            </div>\n   316→\n   317→            <div class=\"item\">\n   318→                <div class=\"item-title\">\n   319→                    <a href=\"https://juejin.cn/post/7611006514892242963\" target=\"_blank\">AI's Next Steps: 5 Trends to Watch in 2026</a>\n   320→                </div>\n   321→                <div class=\"item-description\">\n   322→                    Comprehensive analysis covering the evolution of AI coding agents and specialized LLMs trained for coding scenarios. Key tools discussed include Claude Code, OpenAI Codex, and Qwen3-Coder-Next. Explains how modern agents can understand project structures, dependencies, and debugging processes.\n   323→                </div>\n   324→                <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   325→                    <span class=\"source-badge\">TechMedia</span>\n   326→                    <span>稀土掘金</span>\n   327→                    <span>| 2026-02-27</span>\n   328→                </div>\n   329→                <div>\n   330→                    <span class=\"tag\">AI trends 2026</span>\n   331→                    <span class=\"tag\">AI agents</span>\n   332→                    <span class=\"tag\">specialized LLMs</span>\n   333→                </div>\n   334→            </div>\n   335→\n   336→            <div class=\"item\">\n   337→                <div class=\"item-title\">\n   338→                    <a href=\"https://mp.ofweek.com/ai/a556714706507\" target=\"_blank\">AI Coding Market Analysis: Product Surge But Startup Opportunities Closing</a>\n   339→                </div>\n   340→                <div class=\"item-description\">\n   341→                    Analysis of the AI coding market noting a significant product surge in early 2026, but warning that opportunities for startup founders are rapidly closing as major tech companies acquire or launch competing products. Context includes recent major acquisitions: Cursor completed $900M funding with valuation near $10B, Google acquired Windsurf for $2.4B.\n   342→                </div>\n   343→                <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   344→                    <span class=\"source-badge\">TechMedia</span>\n   345→                    <span>OFweek AI</span>\n   346→                    <span>| 2026-02-26</span>\n   347→                </div>\n   348→                <div>\n   349→                    <span class=\"tag\">AI coding market</span>\n   350→                    <span class=\"tag\">startups</span>\n   351→                    <span class=\"tag\">acquisitions</span>\n   352→                </div>\n   353→            </div>\n   354→\n   355→            <div class=\"item\">\n   356→                <div class=\"item-title\">\n   357→                    <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@Fireship\" target=\"_blank\">Fireship: How to Make Vibe Coding Not Suck - 7 Essential MCP Servers</a>\n   358→                </div>\n   359→                <div class=\"item-description\">\n   360→                    Fireship released a video discussing the current state of AI coding, highlighting how some developers are abandoning AI due to reliability issues while others are significantly boosting productivity. Covers 7 essential MCP servers to avoid the 'prompt hell treadmill' and improve AI coding reliability.\n   361→                </div>\n   362→                <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   363→                    <span class=\"source-badge\">YouTube</span>\n   364→                    <span>Fireship</span>\n   365→                    <span>| 2026-02-25</span>\n   366→                </div>\n   367→                <div>\n   368→                    <span class=\"tag\">Vibe Coding</span>\n   369→                    <span class=\"tag\">MCP servers</span>\n   370→                    <span class=\"tag\">AI coding tools</span>\n   371→                </div>\n   372→            </div>\n   373→\n   374→            <div class=\"item\">\n   375→                <div class=\"item-title\">\n   376→                    <a href=\"https://new.qq.com/rain/a/LNK2025081008329400\" target=\"_blank\">Claude Code Usage Experience - 1.5 Months of Intensive Vibe Coding</a>\n   377→                </div>\n   378→                <div class=\"item-description\">\n   379→                    Detailed analysis of 'Vibe Coding' - deep AI-assisted programming after 1.5 months of intensive Claude Code usage. Explains what tasks LLMs excel at (understanding code logic, creating diagrams, rapid prototyping) and identifies tasks where LLMs struggle (100% accuracy requirements, complex debugging).\n   380→                </div>\n   381→                <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   382→                    <span class=\"source-badge\">TechMedia</span>\n   383→                    <span>喵神 (Miao Shen)</span>\n   384→                    <span>| 2026-02-25</span>\n   385→                </div>\n   386→                <div>\n   387→                    <span class=\"tag\">Claude Code</span>\n   388→                    <span class=\"tag\">Vibe Coding</span>\n   389→                    <span class=\"tag\">LLM capabilities</span>\n   390→                </div>\n   391→            </div>\n   392→\n   393→            <div class=\"item\">\n   394→                <div class=\"item-title\">\n   395→                    <a href=\"https://twitter.com/karpathy\" target=\"_blank\">AI Programming Reached Critical Threshold in December 2025 - Andrej Karpathy</a>\n   396→                </div>\n   397→                <div class=\"item-description\">\n   398→                    Andrej Karpathy declared that AI programming underwent a fundamental qualitative change in December 2025. Before December, he considered coding agents 'basically useless,' but after December 2025, everything changed with significantly improved model quality and stronger long-term consistency. His work pattern shifted from '80% hand-coded + 20% Agent-assisted' to '80% Agent-coded + 20% human refinement'.\n   399→                </div>\n   400→                <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   401→                    <span class=\"source-badge\">Twitter/Blog</span>\n   402→                    <span>Andrej Karpathy</span>\n   403→                    <span>| 2026-02-24</span>\n   404→                </div>\n   405→                <div>\n   406→                    <span class=\"tag\">AI programming</span>\n   407→                    <span class=\"tag\">Vibe Coding</span>\n   408→                    <span class=\"tag\">LLM agents</span>\n   409→                </div>\n   410→            </div>\n   411→\n   412→            <div class=\"item\">\n   413→                <div class=\"item-title\">\n   414→                    <a href=\"https://blog.csdn.net/wangzhao0012/article/details/158349495\" target=\"_blank\">Karpathy's Six Key LLM Breakthroughs of 2025</a>\n   415→                </div>\n   416→                <div class=\"item-description\">\n   417→                    In his annual summary, Karpathy highlighted six major breakthroughs that enabled the AI programming transformation: 1) RLVR (Reinforcement Learning with Verifiable Rewards), 2) Jagged Intelligence, 3) Cursor's Next-Generation Application Layer, 4) Claude Code Local Agents, 5) Vibe Coding, and 6) Nano Banana LLM GUI. He also purchased an M4 Mac Mini to research 'Claws' - an emerging AI agent orchestration layer.\n   418→                </div>\n   419→                <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   420→                    <span class=\"source-badge\">Blog/Twitter</span>\n   421→                    <span>Andrej Karpathy</span>\n   422→                    <span>| 2026-02-24</span>\n   423→                </div>\n   424→                <div>\n   425→                    <span class=\"tag\">LLM breakthroughs</span>\n   426→                    <span class=\"tag\">AI agents</span>\n   427→                    <span class=\"tag\">Vibe Coding</span>\n   428→                </div>\n   429→            </div>\n   430→\n   431→            <div class=\"item\">\n   432→                <div class=\"item-title\">\n   433→                    <a href=\"https://news.qq.com/rain/a/20260224A06NX300\" target=\"_blank\">Stanford Launches Vibe Coding Tutorial - AI Development Course</a>\n   434→                </div>\n   435→                <div class=\"item-description\">\n   436→                    Stanford released a new course offering on 'Coding LLMs and AI Development' covering LLM training principles, effective prompt engineering, open-source tools like GitNexus for reducing AI Coding failure rates, and discussion of how LLM Agent capabilities (especially Claude and Codex) crossed a coherence threshold in late 2025.\n   437→                </div>\n   438→                <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   439→                    <span class=\"source-badge\">TechMedia</span>\n   440→                    <span>Stanford University</span>\n   441→                    <span>| 2026-02-24</span>\n   442→                </div>\n   443→                <div>\n   444→                    <span class=\"tag\">Vibe Coding</span>\n   445→                    <span class=\"tag\">LLM training</span>\n   446→                    <span class=\"tag\">prompt engineering</span>\n   447→                </div>\n   448→            </div>\n   449→\n   450→            <div class=\"item\">\n   451→                <div class=\"item-title\">\n   452→                    <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@lexfridman\" target=\"_blank\">Lex Fridman Podcast #482: Pavel Durov on Freedom, Censorship, and Technology</a>\n   453→                </div>\n   454→                <div class=\"item-description\">\n   455→                    Lex Fridman released episode #482 featuring an in-depth 4 hour 34 minute interview with Telegram founder Pavel Durov. The conversation covers topics including Telegram's philosophy, freedom of speech, censorship, money, power, and human nature in the context of modern technology and AI.\n   456→                </div>\n   457→                <div class=\"item-meta\">\n   458→                    <span class=\"source-badge\">Podcast</span>\n   459→                    <span>Lex Fridman</span>\n   460→                    <span>| 2026-02-24</span>\n   461→                </div>\n   462→                <div>\n   463→                    <span class=\"tag\">AI</span>\n   464→                    <span class=\"tag\">freedom</span>\n   465→                    <span class=\"tag\">censorship</span>\n   466→                </div>\n   467→            </div>\n   468→        </section>\n   469→    </main>\n   470→\n   471→    <footer>\n   472→        <a href=\"#\">Archive</a>\n   473→        <a href=\"#\">About</a>\n   474→        <a href=\"#\">RSS Feed</a>\n   475→        <a href=\"#\">Contact</a>\n   476→        <div style=\"margin-top: 10px;\">© 2026 Agentic Coding Research Report</div>\n   477→    </footer>\n   478→</body>\n   479→</html>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"
